Reflex.SayString:
Congratulations!
You've completed Gawlf: Classic Links!

Might I suggest a medium iron, sir. Line up with the flag, wait until the power meter is a little over 50%, and then hit <X>. If you need to putt the ball the rest of the way, wait until the power meter is 20% full, then hit <X> for a gentle hit.

I would suggest a long iron or medium driver in this case. Use <X> when the power meter is full for a long iron, or use <Y> when the power meter's half-way full. Watch out for that dog leg though, they can be tricky!

Might I suggest a medium driver, Mr. Kodu? Watch out for the water hazard below; a real Pro would bank the ball off that island. Also make sure you don't overpower the ball and overshoot that dog leg.
Might I suggest a long driver, sir? Watch out for those sandtraps. If you get stuck, I suggest using a low power iron <X> to blast it over the lip of the trap.
A low power drive <Y>, or possibly a medium power iron <X> would be appropriate. Just don't overshoot the course!
My goodness, I don't even know where to begin on this one! You're on your own here--why I heard even ol' Brad himself had trouble on this hole!
